  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: dd64eb842f3dd694bae8487ce6510215, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Daniel Taken to Babylon'
      title: Daniel Taken to Babylon
      number: 1
      content: '  In the third year of the reign of Jehoiakim king of Judah, Nebuchadnezzar
        king of Babylon came to Jerusalem and besieged it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the Lord gave Jehoiakim king of Judah into his hand, with some
        of the vessels of the house of God. And he brought them to the land of Shinar,
        to the house of his god, and placed the vessels in the treasury of his god. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then the king commanded Ashpenaz, his chief eunuch, to bring some
        of the people of Israel, both of the royal family[[COMMENT(0)]] and of the
        nobility, '
      comments:
      - number: '1:3 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "youths without blemish, of good appearance and skillful in all wisdom,
        endowed with knowledge, understanding learning, and competent to stand in
        the king\u2019s palace, and to teach them the literature and language of
        the Chaldeans. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The king assigned them a daily portion of the food that the king
        ate, and of the wine that he drank. They were to be educated for three years,
        and at the end of that time they were to stand before the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Among these were Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah of the tribe
        of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: "7: Daniel\u2019s Faithfulness"
      title: "Daniel\u2019s Faithfulness"
      number: 7
      content: 'And the chief of the eunuchs gave them names: Daniel he called Belteshazzar,
        Hananiah he called Shadrach, Mishael he called Meshach, and Azariah he called
        Abednego.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But Daniel resolved that he would not defile himself with the king\u2019s
        food, or with the wine that he drank. Therefore he asked the chief of the
        eunuchs to allow him not to defile himself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And God gave Daniel favor and compassion in the sight of the chief
        of the eunuchs, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and the chief of the eunuchs said to Daniel, \u201CI fear my lord
        the king, who assigned your food and your drink; for why should he see that
        you were in worse condition than the youths who are of your own age? So you
        would endanger my head with the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Daniel said to the steward whom the chief of the eunuchs had
        assigned over Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CTest your servants for ten days; let us be given vegetables
        to eat and water to drink. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then let our appearance and the appearance of the youths who eat
        the king\u2019s food be observed by you, and deal with your servants according
        to what you see.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So he listened to them in this matter, and tested them for ten days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "At the end of ten days it was seen that they were better in appearance
        and fatter in flesh than all the youths who ate the king\u2019s food. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So the steward took away their food and the wine they were to drink,
        and gave them vegetables.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'As for these four youths, God gave them learning and skill in all
        literature and wisdom, and Daniel had understanding in all visions and dreams. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'At the end of the time, when the king had commanded that they should
        be brought in, the chief of the eunuchs brought them in before Nebuchadnezzar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And the king spoke with them, and among all of them none was found
        like Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah. Therefore they stood before
        the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And in every matter of wisdom and understanding about which the king
        inquired of them, he found them ten times better than all the magicians and
        enchanters that were in all his kingdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: And Daniel was there until the first year of King Cyrus.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s Dream"
      title: "Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s Dream"
      number: 1
      content: '  In the second year of the reign of Nebuchadnezzar, Nebuchadnezzar
        had dreams; his spirit was troubled, and his sleep left him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then the king commanded that the magicians, the enchanters, the sorcerers,
        and the Chaldeans be summoned to tell the king his dreams. So they came in
        and stood before the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the king said to them, \u201CI had a dream, and my spirit is
        troubled to know the dream.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the Chaldeans said to the king in Aramaic,[[COMMENT(0)]]  \u201CO
        king, live forever! Tell your servants the dream, and we will show the interpretation.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '2:4 '
        content: The text from this point to the end of chapter 7 is in Aramaic
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The king answered and said to the Chaldeans, \u201CThe word from
        me is firm: if you do not make known to me the dream and its interpretation,
        you shall be torn limb from limb, and your houses shall be laid in ruins. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But if you show the dream and its interpretation, you shall receive
        from me gifts and rewards and great honor. Therefore show me the dream and
        its interpretation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "They answered a second time and said, \u201CLet the king tell his
        servants the dream, and we will show its interpretation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The king answered and said, \u201CI know with certainty that you
        are trying to gain time, because you see that the word from me is firm\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "if you do not make the dream known to me, there is but one sentence
        for you. You have agreed to speak lying and corrupt words before me till
        the times change. Therefore tell me the dream, and I shall know that you
        can show me its interpretation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The Chaldeans answered the king and said, \u201CThere is not a man
        on earth who can meet the king\u2019s demand, for no great and powerful king
        has asked such a thing of any magician or enchanter or Chaldean. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The thing that the king asks is difficult, and no one can show it
        to the king except the gods, whose dwelling is not with flesh.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Because of this the king was angry and very furious, and commanded
        that all the wise men of Babylon be destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So the decree went out, and the wise men were about to be killed;
        and they sought Daniel and his companions, to kill them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Daniel replied with prudence and discretion to Arioch, the captain
        of the king\u2019s guard, who had gone out to kill the wise men of Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "He declared[[COMMENT(0)]] to Arioch, the king\u2019s captain, \u201CWhy
        is the decree of the king so urgent?\u201D Then Arioch made the matter known
        to Daniel. "
      comments:
      - number: '2:15 '
        content: Aramaic ; also verse 26
    - name: "16: God Reveals Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s Dream"
      title: "God Reveals Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s Dream"
      number: 16
      content: 'And Daniel went in and requested the king to appoint him a time,
        that he might show the interpretation to the king.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Daniel went to his house and made the matter known to Hananiah,
        Mishael, and Azariah, his companions, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and told them to seek mercy from the God of heaven concerning this
        mystery, so that Daniel and his companions might not be destroyed with the
        rest of the wise men of Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then the mystery was revealed to Daniel in a vision of the night.
        Then Daniel blessed the God of heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Daniel answered and said:  \u201CBlessed be the name of God forever
        and ever,  to whom belong wisdom and might.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  He changes times and seasons;  he removes kings and sets up kings; 
        he gives wisdom to the wise  and knowledge to those who have understanding;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  he reveals deep and hidden things;  he knows what is in the darkness, 
        and the light dwells with him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "To you, O God of my fathers,  I give thanks and praise,for you have
        given me wisdom and might,and have now made known to me what we asked of
        you,for you have made known to us the king\u2019s matter.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Therefore Daniel went in to Arioch, whom the king had appointed to
        destroy the wise men of Babylon. He went and said thus to him: \u201CDo not
        destroy the wise men of Babylon; bring me in before the king, and I will
        show the king the interpretation.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Arioch brought in Daniel before the king in haste and said thus
        to him: \u201CI have found among the exiles from Judah a man who will make
        known to the king the interpretation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "The king declared to Daniel, whose name was Belteshazzar, \u201CAre
        you able to make known to me the dream that I have seen and its interpretation?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Daniel answered the king and said, \u201CNo wise men, enchanters,
        magicians, or astrologers can show to the king the mystery that the king
        has asked, "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'but there is a God in heaven who reveals mysteries, and he has made
        known to King Nebuchadnezzar what will be in the latter days. Your dream
        and the visions of your head as you lay in bed are these: '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'To you, O king, as you lay in bed came thoughts of what would be
        after this, and he who reveals mysteries made known to you what is to be. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: Daniel Interprets the Dream'
      title: Daniel Interprets the Dream
      number: 30
      content: 'But as for me, this mystery has been revealed to me, not because
        of any wisdom that I have more than all the living, but in order that the
        interpretation may be made known to the king, and that you may know the thoughts
        of your mind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CYou saw, O king, and behold, a great image. This image, mighty
        and of exceeding brightness, stood before you, and its appearance was frightening. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The head of this image was of fine gold, its chest and arms of silver,
        its middle and thighs of bronze, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'its legs of iron, its feet partly of iron and partly of clay. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'As you looked, a stone was cut out by no human hand, and it struck
        the image on its feet of iron and clay, and broke them in pieces. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Then the iron, the clay, the bronze, the silver, and the gold, all
        together were broken in pieces, and became like the chaff of the summer threshing
        floors; and the wind carried them away, so that not a trace of them could
        be found. But the stone that struck the image became a great mountain and
        filled the whole earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CThis was the dream. Now we will tell the king its interpretation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'You, O king, the king of kings, to whom the God of heaven has given
        the kingdom, the power, and the might, and the glory, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "and into whose hand he has given, wherever they dwell, the children
        of man, the beasts of the field, and the birds of the heavens, making you
        rule over them all\u2014you are the head of gold. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Another kingdom inferior to you shall arise after you, and yet a
        third kingdom of bronze, which shall rule over all the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And there shall be a fourth kingdom, strong as iron, because iron
        breaks to pieces and shatters all things. And like iron that crushes, it
        shall break and crush all these. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "And as you saw the feet and toes, partly of potter\u2019s clay and
        partly of iron, it shall be a divided kingdom, but some of the firmness of
        iron shall be in it, just as you saw iron mixed with the soft clay. "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And as the toes of the feet were partly iron and partly clay, so
        the kingdom shall be partly strong and partly brittle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'As you saw the iron mixed with soft clay, so they will mix with one
        another in marriage,[[COMMENT(0)]] but they will not hold together, just
        as iron does not mix with clay. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:43 '
        content: 'Aramaic '
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'And in the days of those kings the God of heaven will set up a kingdom
        that shall never be destroyed, nor shall the kingdom be left to another people.
        It shall break in pieces all these kingdoms and bring them to an end, and
        it shall stand forever, '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: Daniel Is Promoted'
      title: Daniel Is Promoted
      number: 45
      content: "just as you saw that a stone was cut from a mountain by no human
        hand, and that it broke in pieces the iron, the bronze, the clay, the silver,
        and the gold. A great God has made known to the king what shall be after
        this. The dream is certain, and its interpretation sure.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Then King Nebuchadnezzar fell upon his face and paid homage to Daniel,
        and commanded that an offering and incense be offered up to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "The king answered and said to Daniel, \u201CTruly, your God is God
        of gods and Lord of kings, and a revealer of mysteries, for you have been
        able to reveal this mystery.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'Then the king gave Daniel high honors and many great gifts, and made
        him ruler over the whole province of Babylon and chief prefect over all the
        wise men of Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "Daniel made a request of the king, and he appointed Shadrach, Meshach,
        and Abednego over the affairs of the province of Babylon. But Daniel remained
        at the king\u2019s court."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s Golden Image"
      title: "Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s Golden Image"
      number: 1
      content: '  King Nebuchadnezzar made an image of gold, whose height was sixty
        cubits[[COMMENT(0)]] and its breadth six cubits. He set it up on the plain
        of Dura, in the province of Babylon. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:1 '
        content: A was about 18 inches or 45 centimeters
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then King Nebuchadnezzar sent to gather the satraps, the prefects,
        and the governors, the counselors, the treasurers, the justices, the magistrates,
        and all the officials of the provinces to come to the dedication of the image
        that King Nebuchadnezzar had set up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then the satraps, the prefects, and the governors, the counselors,
        the treasurers, the justices, the magistrates, and all the officials of the
        provinces gathered for the dedication of the image that King Nebuchadnezzar
        had set up. And they stood before the image that Nebuchadnezzar had set up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And the herald proclaimed aloud, \u201CYou are commanded, O peoples,
        nations, and languages, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'that when you hear the sound of the horn, pipe, lyre, trigon, harp,
        bagpipe, and every kind of music, you are to fall down and worship the golden
        image that King Nebuchadnezzar has set up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And whoever does not fall down and worship shall immediately be cast
        into a burning fiery furnace.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Fiery Furnace'
      title: The Fiery Furnace
      number: 7
      content: 'Therefore, as soon as all the peoples heard the sound of the horn,
        pipe, lyre, trigon, harp, bagpipe, and every kind of music, all the peoples,
        nations, and languages fell down and worshiped the golden image that King
        Nebuchadnezzar had set up.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Therefore at that time certain Chaldeans came forward and maliciously
        accused the Jews. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "They declared[[COMMENT(0)]] to King Nebuchadnezzar, \u201CO king,
        live forever! "
      comments:
      - number: '3:9 '
        content: Aramaic ; also verses 24, 26
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You, O king, have made a decree, that every man who hears the sound
        of the horn, pipe, lyre, trigon, harp, bagpipe, and every kind of music,
        shall fall down and worship the golden image. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And whoever does not fall down and worship shall be cast into a burning
        fiery furnace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "There are certain Jews whom you have appointed over the affairs of
        the province of Babylon: Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego. These men, O king,
        pay no attention to you; they do not serve your gods or worship the golden
        image that you have set up.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then Nebuchadnezzar in furious rage commanded that Shadrach, Meshach,
        and Abednego be brought. So they brought these men before the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Nebuchadnezzar answered and said to them, \u201CIs it true, O Shadrach,
        Meshach, and Abednego, that you do not serve my gods or worship the golden
        image that I have set up? "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Now if you are ready when you hear the sound of the horn, pipe, lyre,
        trigon, harp, bagpipe, and every kind of music, to fall down and worship
        the image that I have made, well and good.[[COMMENT(0)]] But if you do not
        worship, you shall immediately be cast into a burning fiery furnace. And
        who is the god who will deliver you out of my hands?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:15 '
        content: 'Aramaic lacks '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego answered and said to the king,
        \u201CO Nebuchadnezzar, we have no need to answer you in this matter. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'If this be so, our God whom we serve is able to deliver us from the
        burning fiery furnace, and he will deliver us out of your hand, O king.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:17 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But if not, be it known to you, O king, that we will not serve your
        gods or worship the golden image that you have set up.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then Nebuchadnezzar was filled with fury, and the expression of his
        face was changed against Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego. He ordered the
        furnace heated seven times more than it was usually heated. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And he ordered some of the mighty men of his army to bind Shadrach,
        Meshach, and Abednego, and to cast them into the burning fiery furnace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then these men were bound in their cloaks, their tunics,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        their hats, and their other garments, and they were thrown into the burning
        fiery furnace. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:21 '
        content: The meaning of the Aramaic words rendered and is uncertain; also
          verse 27
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Because the king\u2019s order was urgent and the furnace overheated,
        the flame of the fire killed those men who took up Shadrach, Meshach, and
        Abednego. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And these three men, Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego, fell bound
        into the burning fiery furnace.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then King Nebuchadnezzar was astonished and rose up in haste. He
        declared to his counselors, \u201CDid we not cast three men bound into the
        fire?\u201D They answered and said to the king, \u201CTrue, O king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "He answered and said, \u201CBut I see four men unbound, walking in
        the midst of the fire, and they are not hurt; and the appearance of the fourth
        is like a son of the gods.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Nebuchadnezzar came near to the door of the burning fiery furnace;
        he declared, \u201CShadrach, Meshach, and Abednego, servants of the Most
        High God, come out, and come here!\u201D Then Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego
        came out from the fire. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And the satraps, the prefects, the governors, and the king\u2019s
        counselors gathered together and saw that the fire had not had any power
        over the bodies of those men. The hair of their heads was not singed, their
        cloaks were not harmed, and no smell of fire had come upon them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Nebuchadnezzar answered and said, \u201CBlessed be the God of Shadrach,
        Meshach, and Abednego, who has sent his angel and delivered his servants,
        who trusted in him, and set aside[[COMMENT(0)]] the king\u2019s command,
        and yielded up their bodies rather than serve and worship any god except
        their own God. "
      comments:
      - number: '3:28 '
        content: 'Aramaic '
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Therefore I make a decree: Any people, nation, or language that speaks
        anything against the God of Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego shall be torn
        limb from limb, and their houses laid in ruins, for there is no other god
        who is able to rescue in this way.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Then the king promoted Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego in the province
        of Babylon.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Nebuchadnezzar Praises God'
      title: Nebuchadnezzar Praises God
      number: 1
      content: '    [[COMMENT(0)]] King Nebuchadnezzar to all peoples, nations, and
        languages, that dwell in all the earth: Peace be multiplied to you! '
      comments:
      - number: '4:1 '
        content: '  Ch 3:31 in Aramaic    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'It has seemed good to me to show the signs and wonders that the Most
        High God has done for me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "3: Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s Second Dream"
      title: "Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s Second Dream"
      number: 3
      content: 'How great are his signs,how mighty his wonders!  His kingdom is an
        everlasting kingdom,  and his dominion endures from generation to generation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  [[COMMENT(0)]] I, Nebuchadnezzar, was at ease in my house and prospering
        in my palace. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:4 '
        content: '  Ch 4:1 in Aramaic  '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I saw a dream that made me afraid. As I lay in bed the fancies and
        the visions of my head alarmed me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So I made a decree that all the wise men of Babylon should be brought
        before me, that they might make known to me the interpretation of the dream. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then the magicians, the enchanters, the Chaldeans, and the astrologers
        came in, and I told them the dream, but they could not make known to me its
        interpretation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "At last Daniel came in before me\u2014he who was named Belteshazzar
        after the name of my god, and in whom is the spirit of the holy gods[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014and
        I told him the dream, saying, "
      comments:
      - number: '4:8 '
        content: Or ; also verses 9, 18
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CO Belteshazzar, chief of the magicians, because I know that
        the spirit of the holy gods is in you and that no mystery is too difficult
        for you, tell me the visions of my dream that I saw and their interpretation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The visions of my head as I lay in bed were these: I saw, and behold,
        a tree in the midst of the earth, and its height was great. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The tree grew and became strong, and its top reached to heaven, and
        it was visible to the end of the whole earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Its leaves were beautiful and its fruit abundant, and in it was food
        for all. The beasts of the field found shade under it, and the birds of the
        heavens lived in its branches, and all flesh was fed from it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CI saw in the visions of my head as I lay in bed, and behold,
        a watcher, a holy one, came down from heaven. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "He proclaimed aloud and said thus: \u2018Chop down the tree and lop
        off its branches, strip off its leaves and scatter its fruit. Let the beasts
        flee from under it and the birds from its branches. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But leave the stump of its roots in the earth, bound with a band
        of iron and bronze, amid the tender grass of the field. Let him be wet with
        the dew of heaven. Let his portion be with the beasts in the grass of the
        earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Let his mind be changed from a man\u2019s, and let a beast\u2019s
        mind be given to him; and let seven periods of time pass over him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The sentence is by the decree of the watchers, the decision by the
        word of the holy ones, to the end that the living may know that the Most
        High rules the kingdom of men and gives it to whom he will and sets over
        it the lowliest of men.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Daniel Interprets the Second Dream'
      title: Daniel Interprets the Second Dream
      number: 18
      content: "This dream I, King Nebuchadnezzar, saw. And you, O Belteshazzar,
        tell me the interpretation, because all the wise men of my kingdom are not
        able to make known to me the interpretation, but you are able, for the spirit
        of the holy gods is in you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then Daniel, whose name was Belteshazzar, was dismayed for a while,
        and his thoughts alarmed him. The king answered and said, \u201CBelteshazzar,
        let not the dream or the interpretation alarm you.\u201D Belteshazzar answered
        and said, \u201CMy lord, may the dream be for those who hate you and its
        interpretation for your enemies! "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The tree you saw, which grew and became strong, so that its top reached
        to heaven, and it was visible to the end of the whole earth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "whose leaves were beautiful and its fruit abundant, and in which
        was food for all, under which beasts of the field found shade, and in whose
        branches the birds of the heavens lived\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'it is you, O king, who have grown and become strong. Your greatness
        has grown and reaches to heaven, and your dominion to the ends of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And because the king saw a watcher, a holy one, coming down from
        heaven and saying, \u2018Chop down the tree and destroy it, but leave the
        stump of its roots in the earth, bound with a band of iron and bronze, in
        the tender grass of the field, and let him be wet with the dew of heaven,
        and let his portion be with the beasts of the field, till seven periods of
        time pass over him,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'this is the interpretation, O king: It is a decree of the Most High,
        which has come upon my lord the king, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'that you shall be driven from among men, and your dwelling shall
        be with the beasts of the field. You shall be made to eat grass like an ox,
        and you shall be wet with the dew of heaven, and seven periods of time shall
        pass over you, till you know that the Most High rules the kingdom of men
        and gives it to whom he will. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And as it was commanded to leave the stump of the roots of the tree,
        your kingdom shall be confirmed for you from the time that you know that
        Heaven rules. '
      comments: []
    - name: "27: Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s Humiliation"
      title: "Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s Humiliation"
      number: 27
      content: "Therefore, O king, let my counsel be acceptable to you: break off
        your sins by practicing righteousness, and your iniquities by showing mercy
        to the oppressed, that there may perhaps be a lengthening of your prosperity.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'All this came upon King Nebuchadnezzar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'At the end of twelve months he was walking on the roof of the royal
        palace of Babylon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "and the king answered and said, \u201CIs not this great Babylon,
        which I have built by my mighty power as a royal residence and for the glory
        of my majesty?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "While the words were still in the king\u2019s mouth, there fell a
        voice from heaven, \u201CO King Nebuchadnezzar, to you it is spoken: The
        kingdom has departed from you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "and you shall be driven from among men, and your dwelling shall be
        with the beasts of the field. And you shall be made to eat grass like an
        ox, and seven periods of time shall pass over you, until you know that the
        Most High rules the kingdom of men and gives it to whom he will.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: Nebuchadnezzar Restored'
      title: Nebuchadnezzar Restored
      number: 33
      content: "Immediately the word was fulfilled against Nebuchadnezzar. He was
        driven from among men and ate grass like an ox, and his body was wet with
        the dew of heaven till his hair grew as long as eagles\u2019 feathers, and
        his nails were like birds\u2019 claws.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: '  At the end of the days I, Nebuchadnezzar, lifted my eyes to heaven,
        and my reason returned to me, and I blessed the Most High, and praised and
        honored him who lives forever,  for his dominion is an everlasting dominion,and
        his kingdom endures from generation to generation;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "  all the inhabitants of the earth are accounted as nothing,and he
        does according to his will among the host of heavenand among the inhabitants
        of the earth;  and none can stay his handor say to him, \u201CWhat have you
        done?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'At the same time my reason returned to me, and for the glory of my
        kingdom, my majesty and splendor returned to me. My counselors and my lords
        sought me, and I was established in my kingdom, and still more greatness
        was added to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: Now I, Nebuchadnezzar, praise and extol and honor the King of heaven,
        for all his works are right and his ways are just; and those who walk in
        pride he is able to humble.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Handwriting on the Wall'
      title: The Handwriting on the Wall
      number: 1
      content: '    King Belshazzar made a great feast for a thousand of his lords
        and drank wine in front of the thousand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  Belshazzar, when he tasted the wine, commanded that the vessels
        of gold and of silver that Nebuchadnezzar his father[[COMMENT(0)]] had taken
        out of the temple in Jerusalem be brought, that the king and his lords, his
        wives, and his concubines might drink from them. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:2 '
        content: Or ; also verses 11, 13, 18
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then they brought in the golden vessels that had been taken out of
        the temple, the house of God in Jerusalem, and the king and his lords, his
        wives, and his concubines drank from them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They drank wine and praised the gods of gold and silver, bronze,
        iron, wood, and stone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "  Immediately the fingers of a human hand appeared and wrote on the
        plaster of the wall of the king\u2019s palace, opposite the lampstand. And
        the king saw the hand as it wrote. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the king\u2019s color changed, and his thoughts alarmed him;
        his limbs gave way, and his knees knocked together. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The king called loudly to bring in the enchanters, the Chaldeans,
        and the astrologers. The king declared[[COMMENT(0)]] to the wise men of Babylon,
        \u201CWhoever reads this writing, and shows me its interpretation, shall
        be clothed with purple and have a chain of gold around his neck and shall
        be the third ruler in the kingdom.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '5:7 '
        content: Aramaic ; also verse 10
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then all the king\u2019s wise men came in, but they could not read
        the writing or make known to the king the interpretation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then King Belshazzar was greatly alarmed, and his color changed,
        and his lords were perplexed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The queen,[[COMMENT(0)]] because of the words of the king and his
        lords, came into the banqueting hall, and the queen declared, \u201CO king,
        live forever! Let not your thoughts alarm you or your color change. "
      comments:
      - number: '5:10 '
        content: Or ; twice in this verse
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "There is a man in your kingdom in whom is the spirit of the holy
        gods.[[COMMENT(0)]] In the days of your father, light and understanding and
        wisdom like the wisdom of the gods were found in him, and King Nebuchadnezzar,
        your father\u2014your father the king\u2014made him chief of the magicians,
        enchanters, Chaldeans, and astrologers, "
      comments:
      - number: '5:11 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '12: Daniel Interprets the Handwriting'
      title: Daniel Interprets the Handwriting
      number: 12
      content: "because an excellent spirit, knowledge, and understanding to interpret
        dreams, explain riddles, and solve problems were found in this Daniel, whom
        the king named Belteshazzar. Now let Daniel be called, and he will show the
        interpretation.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Daniel was brought in before the king. The king answered and
        said to Daniel, \u201CYou are that Daniel, one of the exiles of Judah, whom
        the king my father brought from Judah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I have heard of you that the spirit of the gods[[COMMENT(0)]] is
        in you, and that light and understanding and excellent wisdom are found in
        you. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:14 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now the wise men, the enchanters, have been brought in before me
        to read this writing and make known to me its interpretation, but they could
        not show the interpretation of the matter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But I have heard that you can give interpretations and solve problems.
        Now if you can read the writing and make known to me its interpretation,
        you shall be clothed with purple and have a chain of gold around your neck
        and shall be the third ruler in the kingdom.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Daniel answered and said before the king, \u201CLet your gifts
        be for yourself, and give your rewards to another. Nevertheless, I will read
        the writing to the king and make known to him the interpretation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'O king, the Most High God gave Nebuchadnezzar your father kingship
        and greatness and glory and majesty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And because of the greatness that he gave him, all peoples, nations,
        and languages trembled and feared before him. Whom he would, he killed, and
        whom he would, he kept alive; whom he would, he raised up, and whom he would,
        he humbled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But when his heart was lifted up and his spirit was hardened so that
        he dealt proudly, he was brought down from his kingly throne, and his glory
        was taken from him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He was driven from among the children of mankind, and his mind was
        made like that of a beast, and his dwelling was with the wild donkeys. He
        was fed grass like an ox, and his body was wet with the dew of heaven, until
        he knew that the Most High God rules the kingdom of mankind and sets over
        it whom he will. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And you his son,[[COMMENT(0)]]  Belshazzar, have not humbled your
        heart, though you knew all this, '
      comments:
      - number: '5:22 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'but you have lifted up yourself against the Lord of heaven. And the
        vessels of his house have been brought in before you, and you and your lords,
        your wives, and your concubines have drunk wine from them. And you have praised
        the gods of silver and gold, of bronze, iron, wood, and stone, which do not
        see or hear or know, but the God in whose hand is your breath, and whose
        are all your ways, you have not honored.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CThen from his presence the hand was sent, and this writing
        was inscribed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And this is the writing that was inscribed: Mene, Mene, Tekel, and
        Parsin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'This is the interpretation of the matter: Mene, God has numbered[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the days of your kingdom and brought it to an end; '
      comments:
      - number: '5:26 '
        content: 'sounds like the Aramaic for '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Tekel, you have been weighed[[COMMENT(0)]] in the balances and found
        wanting; '
      comments:
      - number: '5:27 '
        content: 'sounds like the Aramaic for '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Peres, your kingdom is divided and given to the Medes and Persians.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:28 '
        content: '(the singular of ) sounds like the Aramaic for and for '
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then Belshazzar gave the command, and Daniel was clothed with purple,
        a chain of gold was put around his neck, and a proclamation was made about
        him, that he should be the third ruler in the kingdom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '  That very night Belshazzar the Chaldean king was killed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '[[COMMENT(0)]] And Darius the Mede received the kingdom, being about
        sixty-two years old.'
      comments:
      - number: '5:31 '
        content: Ch 6:1 in Aramaic
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Daniel and the Lions\u2019 Den"
      title: "Daniel and the Lions\u2019 Den"
      number: 1
      content: '  It pleased Darius to set over the kingdom 120 satraps, to be throughout
        the whole kingdom; '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and over them three high officials, of whom Daniel was one, to whom
        these satraps should give account, so that the king might suffer no loss. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then this Daniel became distinguished above all the other high officials
        and satraps, because an excellent spirit was in him. And the king planned
        to set him over the whole kingdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the high officials and the satraps sought to find a ground for
        complaint against Daniel with regard to the kingdom, but they could find
        no ground for complaint or any fault, because he was faithful, and no error
        or fault was found in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then these men said, \u201CWe shall not find any ground for complaint
        against this Daniel unless we find it in connection with the law of his God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then these high officials and satraps came by agreement[[COMMENT(0)]]
        to the king and said to him, \u201CO King Darius, live forever! "
      comments:
      - number: '6:6 '
        content: Or ; also verses 11, 15
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'All the high officials of the kingdom, the prefects and the satraps,
        the counselors and the governors are agreed that the king should establish
        an ordinance and enforce an injunction, that whoever makes petition to any
        god or man for thirty days, except to you, O king, shall be cast into the
        den of lions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Now, O king, establish the injunction and sign the document, so that
        it cannot be changed, according to the law of the Medes and the Persians,
        which cannot be revoked.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Therefore King Darius signed the document and injunction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When Daniel knew that the document had been signed, he went to his
        house where he had windows in his upper chamber open toward Jerusalem. He
        got down on his knees three times a day and prayed and gave thanks before
        his God, as he had done previously. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then these men came by agreement and found Daniel making petition
        and plea before his God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then they came near and said before the king, concerning the injunction,
        \u201CO king! Did you not sign an injunction, that anyone who makes petition
        to any god or man within thirty days except to you, O king, shall be cast
        into the den of lions?\u201D The king answered and said, \u201CThe thing
        stands fast, according to the law of the Medes and Persians, which cannot
        be revoked.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then they answered and said before the king, \u201CDaniel, who is
        one of the exiles from Judah, pays no attention to you, O king, or the injunction
        you have signed, but makes his petition three times a day.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then the king, when he heard these words, was much distressed and
        set his mind to deliver Daniel. And he labored till the sun went down to
        rescue him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then these men came by agreement to the king and said to the king,
        \u201CKnow, O king, that it is a law of the Medes and Persians that no injunction
        or ordinance that the king establishes can be changed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then the king commanded, and Daniel was brought and cast into the
        den of lions. The king declared[[COMMENT(0)]] to Daniel, \u201CMay your God,
        whom you serve continually, deliver you!\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '6:16 '
        content: Aramaic ; also verse 20
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And a stone was brought and laid on the mouth of the den, and the
        king sealed it with his own signet and with the signet of his lords, that
        nothing might be changed concerning Daniel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then the king went to his palace and spent the night fasting; no
        diversions were brought to him, and sleep fled from him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then, at break of day, the king arose and went in haste to the den
        of lions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "As he came near to the den where Daniel was, he cried out in a tone
        of anguish. The king declared to Daniel, \u201CO Daniel, servant of the living
        God, has your God, whom you serve continually, been able to deliver you from
        the lions?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Daniel said to the king, \u201CO king, live forever! "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "My God sent his angel and shut the lions\u2019 mouths, and they have
        not harmed me, because I was found blameless before him; and also before
        you, O king, I have done no harm.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then the king was exceedingly glad, and commanded that Daniel be
        taken up out of the den. So Daniel was taken up out of the den, and no kind
        of harm was found on him, because he had trusted in his God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And the king commanded, and those men who had maliciously accused
        Daniel were brought and cast into the den of lions\u2014they, their children,
        and their wives. And before they reached the bottom of the den, the lions
        overpowered them and broke all their bones in pieces.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then King Darius wrote to all the peoples, nations, and languages
        that dwell in all the earth: \u201CPeace be multiplied to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I make a decree, that in all my royal dominion people are to tremble
        and fear before the God of Daniel,for he is the living God,enduring forever;his
        kingdom shall never be destroyed,  and his dominion shall be to the end.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "He delivers and rescues;he works signs and wondersin heaven and on
        earth,he who has saved Danielfrom the power of the lions.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: So this Daniel prospered during the reign of Darius and the reign
        of Cyrus the Persian.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Daniel\u2019s Vision of the Four Beasts"
      title: "Daniel\u2019s Vision of the Four Beasts"
      number: 1
      content: '  In the first year of Belshazzar king of Babylon, Daniel saw a dream
        and visions of his head as he lay in his bed. Then he wrote down the dream
        and told the sum of the matter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Daniel declared,[[COMMENT(0)]] \u201CI saw in my vision by night,
        and behold, the four winds of heaven were stirring up the great sea. "
      comments:
      - number: '7:2 '
        content: 'Aramaic '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And four great beasts came up out of the sea, different from one
        another. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The first was like a lion and had eagles\u2019 wings. Then as I looked
        its wings were plucked off, and it was lifted up from the ground and made
        to stand on two feet like a man, and the mind of a man was given to it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And behold, another beast, a second one, like a bear. It was raised
        up on one side. It had three ribs in its mouth between its teeth; and it
        was told, \u2018Arise, devour much flesh.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'After this I looked, and behold, another, like a leopard, with four
        wings of a bird on its back. And the beast had four heads, and dominion was
        given to it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'After this I saw in the night visions, and behold, a fourth beast,
        terrifying and dreadful and exceedingly strong. It had great iron teeth;
        it devoured and broke in pieces and stamped what was left with its feet.
        It was different from all the beasts that were before it, and it had ten
        horns. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The Ancient of Days Reigns'
      title: The Ancient of Days Reigns
      number: 8
      content: 'I considered the horns, and behold, there came up among them another
        horn, a little one, before which three of the first horns were plucked up
        by the roots. And behold, in this horn were eyes like the eyes of a man,
        and a mouth speaking great things.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAs I looked,  thrones were placed,and the Ancient of Days took
        his seat;  his clothing was white as snow,and the hair of his head like pure
        wool;his throne was fiery flames;  its wheels were burning fire.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  A stream of fire issuedand came out from before him;  a thousand
        thousands served him,  and ten thousand times ten thousand stood before him;the
        court sat in judgment,and the books were opened.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CI looked then because of the sound of the great words that
        the horn was speaking. And as I looked, the beast was killed, and its body
        destroyed and given over to be burned with fire. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Son of Man Is Given Dominion'
      title: The Son of Man Is Given Dominion
      number: 12
      content: 'As for the rest of the beasts, their dominion was taken away, but
        their lives were prolonged for a season and a time.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CI saw in the night visions,and behold, with the clouds of heaventhere
        came one like a son of man,and he came to the Ancient of Daysand was presented
        before him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: "14: Daniel\u2019s Vision Interpreted"
      title: "Daniel\u2019s Vision Interpreted"
      number: 14
      content: '  And to him was given dominionand glory and a kingdom,that all peoples,
        nations, and languagesshould serve him;  his dominion is an everlasting dominion,which
        shall not pass away,and his kingdom onethat shall not be destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CAs for me, Daniel, my spirit within me[[COMMENT(0)]] was anxious,
        and the visions of my head alarmed me. "
      comments:
      - number: '7:15 '
        content: 'Aramaic '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I approached one of those who stood there and asked him the truth
        concerning all this. So he told me and made known to me the interpretation
        of the things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018These four great beasts are four kings who shall arise out
        of the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But the saints of the Most High shall receive the kingdom and possess
        the kingdom forever, forever and ever.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CThen I desired to know the truth about the fourth beast, which
        was different from all the rest, exceedingly terrifying, with its teeth of
        iron and claws of bronze, and which devoured and broke in pieces and stamped
        what was left with its feet, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'and about the ten horns that were on its head, and the other horn
        that came up and before which three of them fell, the horn that had eyes
        and a mouth that spoke great things, and that seemed greater than its companions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'As I looked, this horn made war with the saints and prevailed over
        them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'until the Ancient of Days came, and judgment was given for the saints
        of the Most High, and the time came when the saints possessed the kingdom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CThus he said: \u2018As for the fourth beast,there shall be
        a fourth kingdom on earth,which shall be different from all the kingdoms,and
        it shall devour the whole earth,and trample it down, and break it to pieces.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'As for the ten horns,out of this kingdom ten kings shall arise,and
        another shall arise after them;he shall be different from the former ones,and
        shall put down three kings.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  He shall speak words against the Most High,and shall wear out the
        saints of the Most High,and shall think to change the times and the law;and
        they shall be given into his handfor a time, times, and half a time.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '  But the court shall sit in judgment,and his dominion shall be taken
        away,to be consumed and destroyed to the end.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "  And the kingdom and the dominionand the greatness of the kingdoms
        under the whole heavenshall be given to the people of the saints of the Most
        High;  his kingdom shall be an everlasting kingdom,and all dominions shall
        serve and obey him.\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:27 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CHere is the end of the matter. As for me, Daniel, my thoughts
        greatly alarmed me, and my color changed, but I kept the matter in my heart.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Daniel\u2019s Vision of the Ram and the Goat"
      title: "Daniel\u2019s Vision of the Ram and the Goat"
      number: 1
      content: '  In the third year of the reign of King Belshazzar a vision appeared
        to me, Daniel, after that which appeared to me at the first. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And I saw in the vision; and when I saw, I was in Susa the citadel,
        which is in the province of Elam. And I saw in the vision, and I was at the
        Ulai canal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I raised my eyes and saw, and behold, a ram standing on the bank
        of the canal. It had two horns, and both horns were high, but one was higher
        than the other, and the higher one came up last. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I saw the ram charging westward and northward and southward. No beast
        could stand before him, and there was no one who could rescue from his power.
        He did as he pleased and became great.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'As I was considering, behold, a male goat came from the west across
        the face of the whole earth, without touching the ground. And the goat had
        a conspicuous horn between his eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He came to the ram with the two horns, which I had seen standing
        on the bank of the canal, and he ran at him in his powerful wrath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I saw him come close to the ram, and he was enraged against him and
        struck the ram and broke his two horns. And the ram had no power to stand
        before him, but he cast him down to the ground and trampled on him. And there
        was no one who could rescue the ram from his power. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the goat became exceedingly great, but when he was strong, the
        great horn was broken, and instead of it there came up four conspicuous horns
        toward the four winds of heaven.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Out of one of them came a little horn, which grew exceedingly great
        toward the south, toward the east, and toward the glorious land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'It grew great, even to the host of heaven. And some of the host and
        some[[COMMENT(0)]] of the stars it threw down to the ground and trampled
        on them. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:10 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'It became great, even as great as the Prince of the host. And the
        regular burnt offering was taken away from him, and the place of his sanctuary
        was overthrown. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And a host will be given over to it together with the regular burnt
        offering because of transgression,[[COMMENT(0)]] and it will throw truth
        to the ground, and it will act and prosper. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:12 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then I heard a holy one speaking, and another holy one said to the
        one who spoke, \u201CFor how long is the vision concerning the regular burnt
        offering, the transgression that makes desolate, and the giving over of the
        sanctuary and host to be trampled underfoot?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: The Interpretation of the Vision'
      title: The Interpretation of the Vision
      number: 14
      content: "And he said to me,[[COMMENT(0)]] \u201CFor 2,300 evenings and mornings.
        Then the sanctuary shall be restored to its rightful state.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:14 '
        content: 'Hebrew; Septuagint, Theodotion, Vulgate '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When I, Daniel, had seen the vision, I sought to understand it. And
        behold, there stood before me one having the appearance of a man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And I heard a man\u2019s voice between the banks of the Ulai, and
        it called, \u201CGabriel, make this man understand the vision.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So he came near where I stood. And when he came, I was frightened
        and fell on my face. But he said to me, \u201CUnderstand, O son of man, that
        the vision is for the time of the end.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And when he had spoken to me, I fell into a deep sleep with my face
        to the ground. But he touched me and made me stand up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "He said, \u201CBehold, I will make known to you what shall be at
        the latter end of the indignation, for it refers to the appointed time of
        the end. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'As for the ram that you saw with the two horns, these are the kings
        of Media and Persia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the goat[[COMMENT(0)]] is the king of Greece. And the great horn
        between his eyes is the first king. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:21 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'As for the horn that was broken, in place of which four others arose,
        four kingdoms shall arise from his[[COMMENT(0)]] nation, but not with his
        power. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:22 '
        content: 'Theodotion, Septuagint, Vulgate; Hebrew '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And at the latter end of their kingdom, when the transgressors have
        reached their limit, a king of bold face, one who understands riddles, shall
        arise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "His power shall be great\u2014but not by his own power; and he shall
        cause fearful destruction and shall succeed in what he does, and destroy
        mighty men and the people who are the saints. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "By his cunning he shall make deceit prosper under his hand, and in
        his own mind he shall become great. Without warning he shall destroy many.
        And he shall even rise up against the Prince of princes, and he shall be
        broken\u2014but by no human hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "The vision of the evenings and the mornings that has been told is
        true, but seal up the vision, for it refers to many days from now.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And I, Daniel, was overcome and lay sick for some days. Then I rose
        and went about the king\u2019s business, but I was appalled by the vision
        and did not understand it."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Daniel\u2019s Prayer for His People"
      title: "Daniel\u2019s Prayer for His People"
      number: 1
      content: "    In the first year of Darius the son of Ahasuerus, by descent
        a Mede, who was made king over the realm of the Chaldeans\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'in the first year of his reign, I, Daniel, perceived in the books
        the number of years that, according to the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        to Jeremiah the prophet, must pass before the end of the desolations of Jerusalem,
        namely, seventy years.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then I turned my face to the Lord God, seeking him by prayer and
        pleas for mercy with fasting and sackcloth and ashes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I prayed to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God and made confession,
        saying, \u201CO Lord, the great and awesome God, who keeps covenant and steadfast
        love with those who love him and keep his commandments, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'we have sinned and done wrong and acted wickedly and rebelled, turning
        aside from your commandments and rules. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'We have not listened to your servants the prophets, who spoke in
        your name to our kings, our princes, and our fathers, and to all the people
        of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'To you, O Lord, belongs righteousness, but to us open shame, as at
        this day, to the men of Judah, to the inhabitants of Jerusalem, and to all
        Israel, those who are near and those who are far away, in all the lands to
        which you have driven them, because of the treachery that they have committed
        against you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'To us, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, belongs open shame, to our
        kings, to our princes, and to our fathers, because we have sinned against
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'To the Lord our God belong mercy and forgiveness, for we have rebelled
        against him '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and have not obeyed the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God by walking in his laws, which he set before us by his servants the
        prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'All Israel has transgressed your law and turned aside, refusing to
        obey your voice. And the curse and oath that are written in the Law of Moses
        the servant of God have been poured out upon us, because we have sinned against
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He has confirmed his words, which he spoke against us and against
        our rulers who ruled us,[[COMMENT(0)]] by bringing upon us a great calamity.
        For under the whole heaven there has not been done anything like what has
        been done against Jerusalem. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:12 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'As it is written in the Law of Moses, all this calamity has come
        upon us; yet we have not entreated the favor of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God, turning from our iniquities and gaining insight by your truth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has kept ready the calamity
        and has brought it upon us, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God is
        righteous in all the works that he has done, and we have not obeyed his voice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And now, O Lord our God, who brought your people out of the land
        of Egypt with a mighty hand, and have made a name for yourself, as at this
        day, we have sinned, we have done wickedly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CO Lord, according to all your righteous acts, let your anger
        and your wrath turn away from your city Jerusalem, your holy hill, because
        for our sins, and for the iniquities of our fathers, Jerusalem and your people
        have become a byword among all who are around us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now therefore, O our God, listen to the prayer of your servant and
        to his pleas for mercy, and for your own sake, O Lord,[[COMMENT(0)]]  make
        your face to shine upon your sanctuary, which is desolate. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:17 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'O my God, incline your ear and hear. Open your eyes and see our desolations,
        and the city that is called by your name. For we do not present our pleas
        before you because of our righteousness, but because of your great mercy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Gabriel Brings an Answer'
      title: Gabriel Brings an Answer
      number: 19
      content: "O Lord, hear; O Lord, forgive. O Lord, pay attention and act. Delay
        not, for your own sake, O my God, because your city and your people are called
        by your name.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  While I was speaking and praying, confessing my sin and the sin
        of my people Israel, and presenting my plea before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        my God for the holy hill of my God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'while I was speaking in prayer, the man Gabriel, whom I had seen
        in the vision at the first, came to me in swift flight at the time of the
        evening sacrifice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "He made me understand, speaking with me and saying, \u201CO Daniel,
        I have now come out to give you insight and understanding. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: The Seventy Weeks'
      title: The Seventy Weeks
      number: 23
      content: 'At the beginning of your pleas for mercy a word went out, and I have
        come to tell it to you, for you are greatly loved. Therefore consider the
        word and understand the vision.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "  \u201CSeventy weeks[[COMMENT(0)]] are decreed about your people
        and your holy city, to finish the transgression, to put an end to sin, and
        to atone for iniquity, to bring in everlasting righteousness, to seal both
        vision and prophet, and to anoint a most holy place.  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:24 '
        content: 'Or ; also twice in verse 25 and once in verse 26Or , or '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Know therefore and understand that from the going out of the word
        to restore and build Jerusalem to the coming of an anointed one, a prince,
        there shall be seven weeks. Then for sixty-two weeks it shall be built again[[COMMENT(0)]]
        with squares and moat, but in a troubled time. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:25 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And after the sixty-two weeks, an anointed one shall be cut off and
        shall have nothing. And the people of the prince who is to come shall destroy
        the city and the sanctuary. Its[[COMMENT(0)]] end shall come with a flood,
        and to the end there shall be war. Desolations are decreed. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:26 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And he shall make a strong covenant with many for one week,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and for half of the week he shall put an end to sacrifice and offering. And
        on the wing of abominations shall come one who makes desolate, until the
        decreed end is poured out on the desolator.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '9:27 '
        content: Or ; twice in this verse
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Daniel\u2019s Terrifying Vision of a Man"
      title: "Daniel\u2019s Terrifying Vision of a Man"
      number: 1
      content: '    In the third year of Cyrus king of Persia a word was revealed
        to Daniel, who was named Belteshazzar. And the word was true, and it was
        a great conflict.[[COMMENT(0)]] And he understood the word and had understanding
        of the vision.  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:1 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'In those days I, Daniel, was mourning for three weeks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I ate no delicacies, no meat or wine entered my mouth, nor did I
        anoint myself at all, for the full three weeks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'On the twenty-fourth day of the first month, as I was standing on
        the bank of the great river (that is, the Tigris) '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I lifted up my eyes and looked, and behold, a man clothed in linen,
        with a belt of fine gold from Uphaz around his waist. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'His body was like beryl, his face like the appearance of lightning,
        his eyes like flaming torches, his arms and legs like the gleam of burnished
        bronze, and the sound of his words like the sound of a multitude. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And I, Daniel, alone saw the vision, for the men who were with me
        did not see the vision, but a great trembling fell upon them, and they fled
        to hide themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So I was left alone and saw this great vision, and no strength was
        left in me. My radiant appearance was fearfully changed,[[COMMENT(0)]]  and
        I retained no strength. '
      comments:
      - number: '10:8 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then I heard the sound of his words, and as I heard the sound of
        his words, I fell on my face in deep sleep with my face to the ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And behold, a hand touched me and set me trembling on my hands and
        knees. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And he said to me, \u201CO Daniel, man greatly loved, understand
        the words that I speak to you, and stand upright, for now I have been sent
        to you.\u201D And when he had spoken this word to me, I stood up trembling. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then he said to me, \u201CFear not, Daniel, for from the first day
        that you set your heart to understand and humbled yourself before your God,
        your words have been heard, and I have come because of your words. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The prince of the kingdom of Persia withstood me twenty-one days,
        but Michael, one of the chief princes, came to help me, for I was left there
        with the kings of Persia, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and came to make you understand what is to happen to your people
        in the latter days. For the vision is for days yet to come.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When he had spoken to me according to these words, I turned my face
        toward the ground and was mute. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And behold, one in the likeness of the children of man touched my
        lips. Then I opened my mouth and spoke. I said to him who stood before me,
        \u201CO my lord, by reason of the vision pains have come upon me, and I retain
        no strength. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "How can my lord\u2019s servant talk with my lord? For now no strength
        remains in me, and no breath is left in me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Again one having the appearance of a man touched me and strengthened
        me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And he said, \u201CO man greatly loved, fear not, peace be with you;
        be strong and of good courage.\u201D And as he spoke to me, I was strengthened
        and said, \u201CLet my lord speak, for you have strengthened me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then he said, \u201CDo you know why I have come to you? But now I
        will return to fight against the prince of Persia; and when I go out, behold,
        the prince of Greece will come. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But I will tell you what is inscribed in the book of truth: there
        is none who contends by my side against these except Michael, your prince.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Kings of the South and the North'
      title: The Kings of the South and the North
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CAnd as for me, in the first year of Darius the Mede, I stood
        up to confirm and strengthen him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CAnd now I will show you the truth. Behold, three more kings
        shall arise in Persia, and a fourth shall be far richer than all of them.
        And when he has become strong through his riches, he shall stir up all against
        the kingdom of Greece. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then a mighty king shall arise, who shall rule with great dominion
        and do as he wills. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And as soon as he has arisen, his kingdom shall be broken and divided
        toward the four winds of heaven, but not to his posterity, nor according
        to the authority with which he ruled, for his kingdom shall be plucked up
        and go to others besides these.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CThen the king of the south shall be strong, but one of his
        princes shall be stronger than he and shall rule, and his authority shall
        be a great authority. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'After some years they shall make an alliance, and the daughter of
        the king of the south shall come to the king of the north to make an agreement.
        But she shall not retain the strength of her arm, and he and his arm shall
        not endure, but she shall be given up, and her attendants, he who fathered
        her, and he who supported[[COMMENT(0)]] her in those times.  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:6 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CAnd from a branch from her roots one shall arise in his place.
        He shall come against the army and enter the fortress of the king of the
        north, and he shall deal with them and shall prevail. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He shall also carry off to Egypt their gods with their metal images
        and their precious vessels of silver and gold, and for some years he shall
        refrain from attacking the king of the north. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then the latter shall come into the realm of the king of the south
        but shall return to his own land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CHis sons shall wage war and assemble a multitude of great forces,
        which shall keep coming and overflow and pass through, and again shall carry
        the war as far as his fortress. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then the king of the south, moved with rage, shall come out and fight
        against the king of the north. And he shall raise a great multitude, but
        it shall be given into his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And when the multitude is taken away, his heart shall be exalted,
        and he shall cast down tens of thousands, but he shall not prevail. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For the king of the north shall again raise a multitude, greater
        than the first. And after some years[[COMMENT(0)]] he shall come on with
        a great army and abundant supplies.  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:13 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CIn those times many shall rise against the king of the south,
        and the violent among your own people shall lift themselves up in order to
        fulfill the vision, but they shall fail. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then the king of the north shall come and throw up siegeworks and
        take a well-fortified city. And the forces of the south shall not stand,
        or even his best troops, for there shall be no strength to stand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But he who comes against him shall do as he wills, and none shall
        stand before him. And he shall stand in the glorious land, with destruction
        in his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He shall set his face to come with the strength of his whole kingdom,
        and he shall bring terms of an agreement and perform them. He shall give
        him the daughter of women to destroy the kingdom,[[COMMENT(0)]] but it shall
        not stand or be to his advantage. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:17 '
        content: 'Hebrew , or '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Afterward he shall turn his face to the coastlands and shall capture
        many of them, but a commander shall put an end to his insolence. Indeed,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        he shall turn his insolence back upon him. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:18 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then he shall turn his face back toward the fortresses of his own
        land, but he shall stumble and fall, and shall not be found.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CThen shall arise in his place one who shall send an exactor
        of tribute for the glory of the kingdom. But within a few days he shall be
        broken, neither in anger nor in battle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'In his place shall arise a contemptible person to whom royal majesty
        has not been given. He shall come in without warning and obtain the kingdom
        by flatteries. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Armies shall be utterly swept away before him and broken, even the
        prince of the covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And from the time that an alliance is made with him he shall act
        deceitfully, and he shall become strong with a small people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Without warning he shall come into the richest parts[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of the province, and he shall do what neither his fathers nor his fathers\u2019
        fathers have done, scattering among them plunder, spoil, and goods. He shall
        devise plans against strongholds, but only for a time. "
      comments:
      - number: '11:24 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And he shall stir up his power and his heart against the king of
        the south with a great army. And the king of the south shall wage war with
        an exceedingly great and mighty army, but he shall not stand, for plots shall
        be devised against him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Even those who eat his food shall break him. His army shall be swept
        away, and many shall fall down slain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And as for the two kings, their hearts shall be bent on doing evil.
        They shall speak lies at the same table, but to no avail, for the end is
        yet to be at the time appointed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And he shall return to his land with great wealth, but his heart
        shall be set against the holy covenant. And he shall work his will and return
        to his own land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CAt the time appointed he shall return and come into the south,
        but it shall not be this time as it was before. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'For ships of Kittim shall come against him, and he shall be afraid
        and withdraw, and shall turn back and be enraged and take action against
        the holy covenant. He shall turn back and pay attention to those who forsake
        the holy covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Forces from him shall appear and profane the temple and fortress,
        and shall take away the regular burnt offering. And they shall set up the
        abomination that makes desolate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He shall seduce with flattery those who violate the covenant, but
        the people who know their God shall stand firm and take action. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And the wise among the people shall make many understand, though
        for some days they shall stumble by sword and flame, by captivity and plunder. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'When they stumble, they shall receive a little help. And many shall
        join themselves to them with flattery, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'and some of the wise shall stumble, so that they may be refined,
        purified, and made white, until the time of the end, for it still awaits
        the appointed time.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CAnd the king shall do as he wills. He shall exalt himself and
        magnify himself above every god, and shall speak astonishing things against
        the God of gods. He shall prosper till the indignation is accomplished; for
        what is decreed shall be done. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'He shall pay no attention to the gods of his fathers, or to the one
        beloved by women. He shall not pay attention to any other god, for he shall
        magnify himself above all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'He shall honor the god of fortresses instead of these. A god whom
        his fathers did not know he shall honor with gold and silver, with precious
        stones and costly gifts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'He shall deal with the strongest fortresses with the help of a foreign
        god. Those who acknowledge him he shall load with honor. He shall make them
        rulers over many and shall divide the land for a price.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:39 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "  \u201CAt the time of the end, the king of the south shall attack[[COMMENT(0)]]
        him, but the king of the north shall rush upon him like a whirlwind, with
        chariots and horsemen, and with many ships. And he shall come into countries
        and shall overflow and pass through. "
      comments:
      - number: '11:40 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'He shall come into the glorious land. And tens of thousands shall
        fall, but these shall be delivered out of his hand: Edom and Moab and the
        main part of the Ammonites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'He shall stretch out his hand against the countries, and the land
        of Egypt shall not escape. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'He shall become ruler of the treasures of gold and of silver, and
        all the precious things of Egypt, and the Libyans and the Cushites shall
        follow in his train. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'But news from the east and the north shall alarm him, and he shall
        go out with great fury to destroy and devote many to destruction. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: And he shall pitch his palatial tents between the sea and the glorious
        holy mountain. Yet he shall come to his end, with none to help him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Time of the End'
      title: The Time of the End
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CAt that time shall arise Michael, the great prince who has
        charge of your people. And there shall be a time of trouble, such as never
        has been since there was a nation till that time. But at that time your people
        shall be delivered, everyone whose name shall be found written in the book. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And many of those who sleep in the dust of the earth shall awake,
        some to everlasting life, and some to shame and everlasting contempt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And those who are wise shall shine like the brightness of the sky
        above;[[COMMENT(0)]] and those who turn many to righteousness, like the stars
        forever and ever. '
      comments:
      - number: '12:3 '
        content: "Hebrew ; compare Genesis 1:6\u20138"
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But you, Daniel, shut up the words and seal the book, until the time
        of the end. Many shall run to and fro, and knowledge shall increase.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then I, Daniel, looked, and behold, two others stood, one on this
        bank of the stream and one on that bank of the stream. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And someone said to the man clothed in linen, who was above the waters
        of the stream,[[COMMENT(0)]]  \u201CHow long shall it be till the end of
        these wonders?\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '12:6 '
        content: Or ; also verse 7
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And I heard the man clothed in linen, who was above the waters of
        the stream; he raised his right hand and his left hand toward heaven and
        swore by him who lives forever that it would be for a time, times, and half
        a time, and that when the shattering of the power of the holy people comes
        to an end all these things would be finished. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "I heard, but I did not understand. Then I said, \u201CO my lord,
        what shall be the outcome of these things?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He said, \u201CGo your way, Daniel, for the words are shut up and
        sealed until the time of the end. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Many shall purify themselves and make themselves white and be refined,
        but the wicked shall act wickedly. And none of the wicked shall understand,
        but those who are wise shall understand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And from the time that the regular burnt offering is taken away and
        the abomination that makes desolate is set up, there shall be 1,290 days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Blessed is he who waits and arrives at the 1,335 days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But go your way till the end. And you shall rest and shall stand
        in your allotted place at the end of the days.\u201D"
      comments: []
